 Home Mini device &gt; Settings (gear icon).<\/li>\n<li>Go to \u201cAudio\u201d &gt; \u201cPaired Bluetooth devices.\u201d<\/li>\n<li>Select \u201cEnable Pairing Mode.\u201d<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Once paired, your Google Home Mini can receive audio signals directly via Bluetooth \u2014 even without internet access.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0How It Works Without Wi-Fi<\/h2>\n<p>After pairing, you can stream music or audio from your phone or computer just like any standard Bluetooth speaker. However, voice assistant features like Google Assistant or smart home control won\u2019t work without an active Wi-Fi connection.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Limitations to Consider<\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>No voice commands or smart assistant features offline.<\/li>\n<li>Bluetooth pairing must be set up in advance.<\/li>\n<li>No firmware updates or troubleshooting support without Wi-Fi.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>\u00a0Why Use Google Home Mini This Way?<\/h2>\n<p>Using the Home Mini without Wi-Fi is helpful when traveling, during outages, or in areas with unreliable internet. You still get a compact speaker that\u2019s capable of playing music or podcasts through Bluetooth.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Google\u2019s Take on Offline Usage<\/h2>\n<p>Google designed the Home Mini primarily as a cloud-powered voice assistant, but offline Bluetooth use is a lesser-known feature that offers added flexibility. Learn more about the tech behind it on <a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Google_Home\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wikipedia's Google Home article<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Conclusion<\/h2>\n<p>While the Google Home Mini shines with Wi-Fi features, it can still serve as a basic Bluetooth speaker when offline. Just set it up once, pair your device, and enjoy playback wherever you are\u2014even without an internet connection.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Can I Use Google Home Mini as Bluetooth Speaker Without Wi-Fi? Yes, you can use the Google Home Mini as a Bluetoo